text:
The house that we've been building did not
happen overnight.
Nobody works harder than me.
17 years old, I went into the military.
I was a competitive cheerleader.
I was homeless, living in a car in Atlanta.
Wrestling was this way to express myself.
This was my sole purpose in life.
I was born to be a professional wrestler.
The moment I stepped through the ropes,
nothing else exists.

As soon as that music hits, I could run
through a wall.
You don't know what I'm gonna do.
I feel like pressure is a privilege.
All that hard work
building me up to literally kill the fear.
It all mattered.
I'm timeless.
I am hot.
I'm bringing the fire, baby.
Cause we all elite.
